news.title: Tardeo towers: FIR against S D Corporation for 'violations'
news.para: The police have registered an FIR based on the directions of the Girgaum magistrate court. Social worker Vaibhav Gawli had filed a private complaint in the court alleging violations.

news.title: Gurugram: As plaster falls off walls, DLF New Town Heights residents seek an audit
news.para: According to residents, the project has several structural deficiencies, including chunks of plaster and concrete falling off frequently, cracks in balconies and leakage in shafts, which pose threats to their safety.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: Property tax slabs to be amended in panchayats
news.para: A proposal for amendment into existing norms of property tax recovery by panchayats has been put up by panchayat department in state.

news.title: Goa: Bungalow of builder sealed over loan default
news.para: The mamlatdar, on September 22, under the SARFAESI Act, 2002 passed an order directing Moni to vacate the bungalow measuring 7,681sqm, and to hand over possession within 48 hours.

news.title: Vadodara: Three offences lodged against Siddhi Vinayak Developers for cheating buyers
news.para: The fresh offences were registered by the Manjalpur police when three people filed complaints alleging that Patel had taken advances and part payments of properties booked by them, but did not refund the money when he could not conduct work on the sites.

news.title: High-rise buildings come under radar of Hubballi-Dharwad civic body
news.para: If there are complaints from the public about buildings going weak and no measures are taken to strengthen them, HDMC will issue notices to the builders asking them to demolish the building voluntarily.

news.title: Builder can't make slum rehabilitation a farce with no fear of removal: Bombay HC
news.para: A slum rehabilitation project involves "human element" -"the right to shelter"- and is not a charity as the builder profits from them when undertaking such projects with the free sale component, said Justice Kulkarni.

news.title: Maharashtra: E-registration from builder's office gets push, citizens to get papers within 24 hours
news.para: The time taken to deliver the documents by email will now be brought down from the earlier 48 hours to 24 hours, or the next day, officials said.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: PAPs oppose Garjepoti scheme; 650 applied for regularisation
news.para: ​​About 650 project affected persons (PAP) from 95 villages across Navi Mumbai have applied to Cidco for regularization.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body to clear construction debris
news.para: BMC officials said while enforcement squads are conducting random checks in different areas, people should inform the civic body about such violations.

news.title: Punjab to come out with new affordable housing policy
news.para: The draft of 'Punjab Affordable Housing Policy-2022' has been uploaded on the official website for seeking suggestions from the public, he said.

news.title: CBI files charge sheet against DHFL's ex-CMD Kapil Wadhawan, 74 others
news.para: In its charge sheet filed before a Special CBI court here, the agency has also named then director Dheeraj Wadhawan and former CEO Harshil Mehta as accused in the mega-scam case, they said.

news.title: ED attaches over Rs 1,300 crore worth assets in money laundering case against IREO, promoters
news.para: ​The attached properties include land, commercial spaces, plots, residential houses and bank accounts, the federal agency said in a statement issued on Saturday. The total value of these attached properties is Rs 1,317.30 crore.

news.title: Urban planning must focus on job creation: Housing Secretary
news.para: The secretary said that affordable housing would come up in urban areas, and it is the responsibility for industry and urban planners to ensure that the development of low-cost homes happens in an organised manner.

news.title: Bombay HC allows Godrej to challenge Rs 264 crore land deal for bullet train
news.para: A bench of Justices Nitin Jamdar and Sharmila Deshmukh, permitting the company to amend a pending 2019 petition in two working days, will now hear the plea for interim relief next week.
